node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Golden State Warriors on August 13, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'மலவ WELCOME ATKINSON KENNY GOLDEN STATE WARRIORS'.

node.text:
OFFICIAL: Kenny Atkinson, Jama Mahlalela, and DeJan Milojević have been added to Head Coach Steve Kerr’s staff.

Kenny joins the Warriors after spending the 2020-21 season as an assistant coach with the Los Angeles Clippers. Previously, he spent three-plus seasons as head coach of the Brooklyn Nets.

Jama recently completed his second stint as an assistant coach with the Toronto Raptors during the 2020-21 season. He spent two seasons (2018-20) as head coach for Raptors 905 in the NBA G League.

Dejan spent the 2021 season as head coach of KK Budućnost in the Adriatic League in Montenegro. Prior to KK Budućnost, he served as the head coach for KK Mega Basket in Belgrade, Serbia, for eight seasons (2012-20).
